Default calibration corpus: WikiText-2 (raw)
============================================

`wikitext2.txt` in this directory is a ~900 KB excerpt of the WikiText-2 (raw)
dataset. PonyExl3 uses it as the default activation-calibration corpus for the
one-command `ponyexl3-convert` pipeline, so a conversion works offline without
the user supplying their own text.

Source : Salesforce/wikitext, configuration `wikitext-2-raw-v1`
         (https://huggingface.co/datasets/Salesforce/wikitext), derived from
         Wikipedia.
Dataset : Merity, Xiong, Bradbury, Socher, "Pointer Sentinel Mixture Models"
         (2016), arXiv:1609.07843.
License : Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 (CC BY-SA 3.0)
         https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/

Modification: a contiguous subset of the `train` split was concatenated into a
single UTF-8 text file; no content was otherwise altered. This excerpt is
redistributed under CC BY-SA 3.0. The rest of PonyExl3 is licensed separately
(see the repository LICENSE); this file's license applies only to this corpus.

To calibrate on your own (e.g. domain-specific) text instead, pass
`--calibration-text <file>`.
